How to install add-ons in Jira step by step
EazyBI Installation
High level architecture
Users (Browser) -> Jira Data Center (4 nodes) -> eazyBI app (plugin) -> eazyBI Database (External DB – Recommended)
•	eazyBI does NOT use the Jira database
•	eazyBI maintains its own analytics database (OLAP)
•	This protects Jira performance and stability [docs.eazybi.com]

Supported Databases for eazyBI (Data Center)
eazyBI requires a dedicated database. Supported options include: [docs.eazybi.com]
•	PostgreSQL 10–17 (recommended)
•	MySQL 8.x
•	Microsoft SQL Server 2016+
•	Oracle 12c R2+
PostgreSQL is most commonly used in Jira DC environments

IMPORTANT DESIGN RULES (Do Not Skip)
•	Do NOT store eazyBI data in Jira’s DB
•	Use a separate external database
•	Same eazyBI DB is shared by all 4 Jira nodes
•	Use a DB user dedicated to eazyBI
o	Database
o	User/schema

PREPARE THE EAZYBI DATABASE
•	DOWNLOAD & INSTALL POSTGRESQL ON WINDOWS
•	Go to https://www.postgresql.org/download/windows/
•	Click on download the installer
•	Choose version 15 and download (as our jira current version support version 15)
•	Now right click on downloaded file and run as administrator
•	Installation Directory
C:\Program Files\PostgreSQL\15
•	Data Directory
C:\PostgreSQL\data
•	Components (select all):
o	PostgreSQL Server 
o	pgAdmin 4 
o	Command Line Tools
•	Set PostgreSQL Superuser Password
You will be asked to set a password for user postgres.
o	Choose a strong password
o	Save it securely
o	This is used only for DB admin tasks
•	Port Configuration
Use default:	Port: 5432
Make sure port 5432 is allowed through firewall.
•	Locale : Default
•	Proceed and complete installation.
•	PostgreSQL service will start automatically

FIREWALL & NETWORK CONFIGURATION
•	Go to windows
•	Now search windows Defender Firewall
•	Now click on advance settings
•	Now click on inbound rule
•	Now click on New Rule
•	Now select port and click on next
•	Now select TCP
•	Specify the local ports : 5432
•	Now click on next
•	Now select allow the connection and click on next
•	Now only check Domain and Private and click on next
•	Now type the name as PostgreSQL 5432
•	Now click on finish

CONFIGURE POSTGRESQL FOR REMOTE ACCESS
By default, PostgreSQL allows local connections only.
To Edit postgresql.conf follow the below steps
•	Go to C:\PostgreSQL\data\postgresql.conf
•	Right click and open in notepad
•	Find and change:
listen_addresses = '*'
•	Now save the file and exit
•	It will allow remote connections

To Allow Jira node to connect  PostgreSQL Edit pg_hba.conf file
•	Go to C:\PostgreSQL\data\pg_hba.conf
•	Right click and open the file in notepad
•	# Allow Jira nodes to connect
host    all    all    <JIRA_SUBNET>/24    md5
example : host    all    all    10.10.20.0/24    md5
•	Replace subnet with your Jira servers’ network

Now Restart PostgreSQL Service
•	Now click windows
•	Type services
•	Restart PostgreSQL 15

CREATE DATABASE AND USER FOR EAZYBI
•	Now open pgAdmin 4
•	Connect to server: 
•	Host: localhost
•	User: postgres (Super User set earlier while installing postgres)
•	Password: (password set earlier while installing postgres)
•	Now click on Query toll and type below queries
o	CREATE USER eazybi_user WITH PASSWORD 'StrongPassword123!';
o	CREATE DATABASE eazybi WITH OWNER = eazybi_user ENCODING = 'UTF8';
o	GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE eazybi TO eazybi_user;
•	Now Run the Query

Note : 
•	Use a strong password
•	Do not reuse Jira DB credentials
•	UTF 8 is mandatory for eazyBI
•	Ensures eazyBI can create schemas and tables by providing privileges

Now validate the connection from the JIRA
Before configuring eazyBI, test connectivity from a Jira node.
•	Now come to JIRA Server
•	Open Telnet or powershell
•	Type the below command
o	Test-NetConnection dbserver.company.com -Port 5432 
•	Should return TcpTestSucceeded : True

INSTALL EAZYBI APP IN JIRA DC
•	Log in as Jira System Admin
•	Navigate to:
•	Administration → Manage apps
•	Click Find new apps
•	Search for EazyBI for Jira
•	Install the app
•	Data Center installs it cluster wide automatically.  Means it will get installed automatically on all the nodes.
•	After install, Jira will start eazyBI as part of the Jira JVM 
•	First startup may take a few minutes
•	You can verify startup in:
o	<JIRA_HOME>/log/atlassian-jira.log

Configure Database Connection
•	Now open Jira
•	Click on EazyBI
•	Click on settings in EazyBI
•	Now in the general Tab
•	Database Type : PostgreSQL
•	Host : IP address of PostgreSQL which was created for EazyBI
•	Port : 5432
•	Database : eazybi
•	Username : eazybi_user
•	Password : password which you use to create eazybi_user account
•	Encoding : UTF 8
•	Give Check mark on SSL
•	Dedicate node : Select the node which you created for PostgreSQL
•	Child process
o	Port : 3801
o	JVM Options:   -Xms2g  -Xmx4g
•	Now in the advance settings
•	Search [source_application] and add
min_regular_import_frequency = "1 day"
cancel_orphan_jobs_interval = "3 hours"
•	If you want to change anything just refer this document
https://docs.eazybi.com/eazybi/set-up-and-administer/atlassian-data-center/advanced-settings
•	Now click on save configuration
•	Now in the restart jira

CREATE EAZYBI ACCOUNT & IMPORT DATA
•	Go to: Apps → eazyBI 
•	Click Create new account 
•	Select: 
o	Source: Jira
o	Projects: Select required projects

Initial Data Import
•	Inside eazyBI account → Source Data
•	Click Import
•	First import: 
o	Can take time (depends on Jira size)
o	Loads history, fields, workflows, transitions
•	Data is stored in OLAP cubes inside the external database.

HOW DATA IS STORED (IMPORTANT FOR AUDIT)
What eazyBI Stores
•	Issues & history snapshots
•	 Measures (time, effort, counts)
•	 Dimensions (Projects, Users, Status, Time, etc.)
•	 Custom fields (if enabled)

What eazyBI Does NOT Store
•	Jira credentials
•	User passwords
•	Realtime transactional data
Data is read only pulled from Jira through APIs, then transformed into analytical structures.
Note : Above we have selected port and JVM
Port
The child process will listen on this TCP/IP port for requests from the eazyBI plugin. By default, port number 3801 is suggested. If you run several Jira instances with the eazyBI plugin on the same server, then specify a different port number in each instance.
JVM options
Additional JVM options that you want to use for the child JVM process. By default, the following options are used: -Xms2g (initial JVM heap size 2GB). However, we recommend using at least 4GB: -Xmx4g (set max JVM heap size to 4GB) for a production environment. Many out of memory errors in logs might indicate insufficient memory.

